  "prompt": "Am I being judgmental if I tell a person that he/she is judgmental?",
  "response": "That's an interesting philosophical question! By pointing out someone's judgmental behavior, you could be seen as being judgmental yourself. The irony is that the act of calling someone judgmental is, in itself, a form of judgment. \n\nThe key might be in how you approach the conversation:\n- If you say it accusingly or critically, then yes, you're being judgmental\n- If you say it constructively and with empathy, trying to help the person become more self-aware, then it's more like feedback\n\nUltimately, the intention and tone behind your statement matters more than the statement itself.",
